properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 1 at 2:58PM MST until February 3 at 9:00PM MST by NWS Albuquerque NM
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts of 60 to 70 mph
possible.

* WHERE...West Central Plateau, West Central Mountains,
Southwest Mountains, South Central Highlands, Upper Tularosa
Valley, South Central Mountains, Eastern Lincoln County,
Southwest Chaves County and San Agustin Plains and Adjacent
Lowlands.

* WHEN...From Monday morning through Monday evening.

* IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property and
cause power outages. Travel could be difficult especially for
high profile vehicles. This includes Interstate 40 and U.S.
Highway 60 from the continental divide to the Arizona border.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Strong winds may combine with rain and snow
from Gallup down to the Gila through McKinley, Cibola, and
Catron Counties. This will create lower visibility for those
traveling in these areas Monday afternoon.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM MONDAY MORNING THROUGH MONDAY EVENING
